1912
01:12:44,626 --> 01:12:46,528
He really doesn't want to be banned.

1913
01:12:46,595 --> 01:12:49,498
There's a way to eat this,
so let me show you.

1914
01:12:49,565 --> 01:12:52,134
You'll find sushi rice down here.

1915
01:12:52,201 --> 01:12:53,869
I've never seen him serve food like that.

1916
01:12:54,603 --> 01:12:56,572
THE FIRST BITE,
EGG, ABALONE, BEEF, AND OCTOPUS

1917
01:12:56,638 --> 01:12:58,507
It's fun to pick and choose.

1918
01:12:58,574 --> 01:13:01,009
-It's like…
-What's that spray?

1919
01:13:01,076 --> 01:13:03,645
-Soy sauce.
-You sprayed it on the spoon?

1920
01:13:03,712 --> 01:13:07,015
It'll taste too salty
if he had it normally.

1921
01:13:07,082 --> 01:13:09,318
If he sprays it on, it can spread evenly.

1922
01:13:09,385 --> 01:13:11,653
Wait, this reminds me
of what happened to Manager Park.

1923
01:13:11,720 --> 01:13:13,689
-Wait a second.
-It's what Moon-jung did.

1924
01:13:13,756 --> 01:13:14,890
Was that necessary?

1925
01:13:14,957 --> 01:13:17,693
She stayed right next to Manager Park.

1926
01:13:18,927 --> 01:13:21,964
He watched her last week and learned.

1927
01:13:22,898 --> 01:13:24,133
What's it like?

1928
01:13:24,199 --> 01:13:25,300
SAVORING THE FLAVOR SLOWLY

1929
01:13:25,868 --> 01:13:27,336
Say something.

1930
01:13:28,270 --> 01:13:31,039
-What?
-He must be thinking.

1931
01:13:31,106 --> 01:13:33,142
-The ChoiPT reviews.
-ChoiPT.

1932
01:13:33,208 --> 01:13:36,378
-It's about time he used one of the lines.
-He already skipped one.

1933
01:13:36,445 --> 01:13:38,147
He's trying to decide if that one line

1934
01:13:38,213 --> 01:13:39,982
-ChoiPT gave him suits this.
-It's this or the next.

1935
01:13:40,048 --> 01:13:42,117
He'll probably go
with Lee Kang-in or Kim Min-jae.

1936
01:13:42,951 --> 01:13:46,021
I really like rice bowls
served with toppings.

1937
01:13:46,088 --> 01:13:49,024
And I also love Japanese food.

1938
01:13:49,091 --> 01:13:54,229
<i>This dish includes everything good,</i>
<i>steak, octopus, eel, abalone, and more.</i>

1939
01:13:54,296 --> 01:13:58,100
But something
that's connecting all these dots

1940
01:13:58,167 --> 01:14:00,636
-seems to be the egg.
-I see.

1941
01:14:00,702 --> 01:14:01,937
It may seem insignificant,

1942
01:14:02,004 --> 01:14:05,707
but it brings all these flavors together

1943
01:14:05,774 --> 01:14:07,876
like the role of midfielders.

1944
01:14:07,943 --> 01:14:11,747
-Egg garnish is called <i>jidan</i>, like Zidane.
-The soccer player?

1945
01:14:11,814 --> 01:14:15,384
I want to mention Lee Kang-in,
who's even better than Zidane.

1946
01:14:15,451 --> 01:14:17,786
We're looking forward
to seeing him in this World Cup.

1947
01:14:17,853 --> 01:14:21,523
So the egg brings
all the ingredients together.

1948
01:14:21,590 --> 01:14:22,624
It goes well with eel,

1949
01:14:23,192 --> 01:14:26,228
as well as the octopus and abalone.
They all blend in.

1950
01:14:26,295 --> 01:14:29,097
That's how important
Kang-in is for the World Cup.

1951
01:14:29,164 --> 01:14:31,266
He'll connect all the dots.

1952
01:14:31,333 --> 01:14:33,101
-The egg plays a big role, then.
-Right?

1953
01:14:33,168 --> 01:14:35,671
That was the food review
as told by ChoiPT.

1954
01:14:35,737 --> 01:14:36,839
He finally used it.

1955
01:14:36,905 --> 01:14:38,307
-Not bad.
-He used it all.

1956
01:14:38,373 --> 01:14:39,875
-He used everything up.
-Everything.

1957
01:14:39,942 --> 01:14:41,844
-He has one more.
-He does?

1958
01:14:41,910 --> 01:14:42,911
Let's wait for it.

1959
01:14:42,978 --> 01:14:44,847
-Is this shrimp?
-It is.

1960
01:14:44,913 --> 01:14:46,014
-Shrimp, out.
-"Shrimp, out."

1961
01:14:46,081 --> 01:14:47,382
Does he not eat shrimp?

1962
01:14:47,449 --> 01:14:50,652
When you eat <i>chirashi </i>sushi,

1963
01:14:50,719 --> 01:14:52,988
you can enjoy different flavors

1964
01:14:53,055 --> 01:14:54,656
by trying different combinations.

1965
01:14:54,723 --> 01:14:57,693
It's like Kang-in making
many different types of passes.

1966
01:14:57,759 --> 01:14:59,027
Yes, it seems so.

1967
01:14:59,094 --> 01:14:59,962
FOCUSED

1968
01:15:00,462 --> 01:15:02,197
SLIPS

1969
01:15:02,564 --> 01:15:04,500
He received a pass,
but he couldn't keep the ball.

1970
01:15:04,733 --> 01:15:06,468
PFFT

1971
01:15:06,535 --> 01:15:09,938
-The food just slipped off.
-Don't mention something like that!

1972
01:15:10,439 --> 01:15:13,141
OH, MAN…

1973
01:15:13,542 --> 01:15:15,644
JUST WHEN EVERYONE WAS ABOUT TO FORGET…

1974
01:15:17,079 --> 01:15:19,047
-What's the squid like?
-What?

1975
01:15:19,114 --> 01:15:21,183
I mean the octopus.

1976
01:15:21,250 --> 01:15:25,554
<i>-That went through three different steps.</i>
<i>-Parboiling, boiling down in sauce,</i>

1977
01:15:25,621 --> 01:15:27,322
<i>and grilling it in a pan.</i>

1978
01:15:27,389 --> 01:15:32,261
It's like a player who can score quickly
in a short amount of time.

1979
01:15:32,327 --> 01:15:34,396
I really loved the first bite.

1980
01:15:35,797 --> 01:15:40,269
But among everything,
it was the juicy steak.

1981
01:15:40,335 --> 01:15:42,137
-It made such an impact.
-Did it taste luxurious?

1982
01:15:42,204 --> 01:15:44,439
-It did.
-He put lots of work into it.

1983
01:15:44,506 --> 01:15:49,044
It's fun to tackle everything,
eel, shrimp, octopus, and abalone,

1984
01:15:49,111 --> 01:15:51,980
as I take over one after the other.

1985
01:15:52,047 --> 01:15:53,916
-I see.
-It's like soccer.

1986
01:15:53,982 --> 01:15:56,118
How far can it make it in the World Cup?

1987
01:15:56,184 --> 01:15:59,021
It'll easily make it into the Round of 16.

1988
01:16:00,022 --> 01:16:03,125
Kang-in will work as the egg garnish.

1989
01:16:03,191 --> 01:16:05,861
-Next, the <i>dureup doenjang-guk.</i>
-<i>Dureup doenjang-guk.</i>

1990
01:16:05,928 --> 01:16:09,164
Ho-young looks anxious and nervous.

1991
01:16:09,231 --> 01:16:10,899
He could get banned from social media.

1992
01:16:12,401 --> 01:16:14,036
I wonder what that's like.

1993
01:16:14,570 --> 01:16:16,338
<i>Dureup doenjang-guk.</i>

1994
01:16:16,405 --> 01:16:18,073
Which <i>doenjang </i>did you use?

1995
01:16:18,140 --> 01:16:21,443
The one you had at home.

1996
01:16:21,510 --> 01:16:24,379
-What you had.
-We can't use anything else.

1997
01:16:24,446 --> 01:16:26,982
We have no choice
but to use your <i>doenjang</i>.

1998
01:16:27,049 --> 01:16:29,117
That's the rule here.
We should be asking you.

1999
01:16:29,184 --> 01:16:31,587
I'm a bit out of it
because this tastes so fantastic.

2000
01:16:31,653 --> 01:16:33,288
He expresses his feelings paradoxically.

2001
01:16:33,355 --> 01:16:37,092
Japanese meals usually come
with miso soup, right?

2002
01:16:37,159 --> 01:16:39,695
The <i>dureup</i> he added

2003
01:16:39,761 --> 01:16:42,497
gave the soup a deep flavor.

2004
01:16:42,564 --> 01:16:44,833
I want to eat this

2005
01:16:44,900 --> 01:16:48,937
and hope that our team does well
without allowing any goals.

2006
01:16:49,004 --> 01:16:50,238
I see.

2007
01:16:50,872 --> 01:16:54,142
I don't think that line was prepared.

2008
01:16:54,209 --> 01:16:57,245
-It wasn't particularly touching.
-No.

2009
01:16:57,312 --> 01:17:00,182
-He had to think of something on the spot.
-Right.

2010
01:17:00,248 --> 01:17:02,751
I think Min-jae would love this too.

2011
01:17:02,818 --> 01:17:05,120
Something Min-jae would love?

2012
01:17:05,187 --> 01:17:07,489
Did you prepare something with him in it?

2013
01:17:07,556 --> 01:17:09,124
-Not Min-jae?
-No.

2014
01:17:09,191 --> 01:17:10,592
Do you have anything else left?

2015
01:17:10,659 --> 01:17:12,260
-He does.
-He does have more?

2016
01:17:12,327 --> 01:17:14,363
Someone who played for Madrid.

2017
01:17:14,429 --> 01:17:17,766
-You can't just share it.
-Which player from Madrid?

2018
01:17:17,833 --> 01:17:19,568
-Bellingham?
-Yes.

2019
01:17:20,068 --> 01:17:21,503
He still has Bellingham left?

2020
01:17:21,570 --> 01:17:24,740
I wonder if the duck will suit that line.

2021
01:17:24,806 --> 01:17:26,174
He has Bellingham left?

2022
01:17:26,241 --> 01:17:29,011
HOW WILL BELLINGHAM
CONNECT WITH HYUN-SUK'S DISH?

2023
01:17:29,077 --> 01:17:30,746
<i>Presen-ducking to the CEO.</i>

2024
01:17:30,812 --> 01:17:34,182
DUCK STEAK WITH ORANGE & CARROT PURÉE

2025
01:17:34,983 --> 01:17:38,654
ASPARAGUS GRATIN AND TANGY ORANGE SAUCE

2026
01:17:39,521 --> 01:17:43,692
CHEF CHOI HYUN-SUK'S
PRESENT-DUCKING TO THE CEO

2027
01:17:43,759 --> 01:17:45,360
-He's coming this way too.
-He is.

2028
01:17:45,427 --> 01:17:46,461
What is this?

2029
01:17:46,528 --> 01:17:50,298
The chef must be the server
to raise his prestige.

2030
01:17:50,365 --> 01:17:52,134
I am Choi Hyun-suk, the head chef.

2031
01:17:52,200 --> 01:17:53,402
The head chef is here.

2032
01:17:53,468 --> 01:17:54,736
We had a head chef?

2033
01:17:54,803 --> 01:17:56,705
-Your dish today…
-Yes?

2034
01:17:56,772 --> 01:17:59,941
…is your usual,
duck steak for your stamina.

2035
01:18:01,376 --> 01:18:04,813
-This is orange sauce.
-Orange sauce.

2036
01:18:04,880 --> 01:18:05,947
Orange goes well with duck.

2037
01:18:06,014 --> 01:18:07,716
They have to.

2038
01:18:07,783 --> 01:18:11,386
Will it be good enough
to stop Ho-young from posting selfies?

2039
01:18:11,453 --> 01:18:15,624
You can try it as is,
then with the purée, and the gratin.

2040
01:18:15,691 --> 01:18:17,592
YUM

2041
01:18:17,659 --> 01:18:19,528
He put lots of work into the duck.

2042
01:18:19,594 --> 01:18:22,330
He's a big fan of duck.

2043
01:18:22,898 --> 01:18:26,034
He likes spicy marinated duck too.

2044
01:18:26,101 --> 01:18:28,070
It's been cooked well.

2045
01:18:28,970 --> 01:18:31,339
We're now waiting for Bellingham.

2046
01:18:31,840 --> 01:18:33,308
Will he go well with the duck?

2047
01:18:33,375 --> 01:18:35,010
FEELING DIZZY WITH THE ATTACKS

2048
01:18:35,077 --> 01:18:38,413
-How will he connect the two?
-How will he do that?

2049
01:18:39,548 --> 01:18:41,450
TAKES ANOTHER BITE OF THE DUCK STEAK

2050
01:18:41,516 --> 01:18:42,784
He's devouring it.

2051
01:18:42,851 --> 01:18:45,987
He knows what he likes and goes for it.

2052
01:18:46,054 --> 01:18:49,691
-The Eagle.
-Look how energetic he seems.

2053
01:18:49,758 --> 01:18:51,993
POWER

2054
01:18:52,527 --> 01:18:53,795
DUCK AUTOMATICALLY GIVES HIM POWER

2055
01:18:53,862 --> 01:18:56,498
That's the way he was eight years ago,

2056
01:18:56,565 --> 01:18:58,433
full of stamina.

2057
01:18:58,500 --> 01:19:02,104
Duck meat is usually greasy, right?

2058
01:19:02,170 --> 01:19:04,539
-But the grease is all gone.
-It's all gone?

2059
01:19:04,606 --> 01:19:07,542
I tried my best to get rid of it
by flipping it and then pressing it down.

2060
01:19:08,677 --> 01:19:10,412
What about the orange sauce?

2061
01:19:10,479 --> 01:19:13,181
-It's not bad.
-It's not bad?

2062
01:19:13,248 --> 01:19:14,950
Just like <i>Oranje</i>.

2063
01:19:15,016 --> 01:19:18,487
-You mean the Dutch national team?
-The Netherlands?

2064
01:19:18,553 --> 01:19:21,123
Bellingham, <i>Oranje</i>, and the Netherlands.

2065
01:19:21,189 --> 01:19:23,825
He keeps thinking and thinking.

2066
01:19:23,892 --> 01:19:26,428
He's trying to figure out
a really nice review.

2067
01:19:26,495 --> 01:19:28,930
Well, you know.

2068
01:19:28,997 --> 01:19:30,665
Not only is the meat nice,

2069
01:19:30,732 --> 01:19:32,234
but the sauce is the kick

2070
01:19:32,300 --> 01:19:35,871
that could break through
the opponent's press.

2071
01:19:35,937 --> 01:19:39,040
Our national team right now
is excellent at beating the press.

2072
01:19:39,875 --> 01:19:41,009
The burst of speed.

2073
01:19:41,076 --> 01:19:43,845
Yes, this sauce is playing that part.

2074
01:19:45,080 --> 01:19:47,849
Someone like Kang-in
never loses the ball, right?

2075
01:19:47,916 --> 01:19:49,851
You already did Kang-in,
so use someone else.

2076
01:19:49,918 --> 01:19:51,820
He's going to get sick.

2077
01:19:51,887 --> 01:19:54,055
He looks like he's about to get sick.

2078
01:19:54,122 --> 01:19:55,824
There's no pressure.

2079
01:19:56,124 --> 01:19:58,360
THE CEO HAS A WEAKNESS AGAINST PRESSURE

2080
01:19:58,426 --> 01:20:02,097
-You'll get new ideas after trying gratin.
-Why don't you try it?

2081
01:20:02,164 --> 01:20:04,065
-Try the gratin.
-Time for the gratin.

2082
01:20:04,132 --> 01:20:07,269
Many players are waiting

2083
01:20:07,335 --> 01:20:10,172
for Manager Choi to mention their name.

2084
01:20:10,238 --> 01:20:11,973
WHAT WILL CHOIPT SAY?

2085
01:20:12,040 --> 01:20:13,508
What's the gratin like?

2086
01:20:14,509 --> 01:20:17,212
-The 2026 World Cup!
-The first bite tasted like…

2087
01:20:17,479 --> 01:20:18,980
ANTICIPATION

2088
01:20:19,047 --> 01:20:21,550
…Heung-min getting past
two or three players

2089
01:20:21,616 --> 01:20:25,020
and kicking a powerful shot
that rips the opponent's net.

2090
01:20:25,086 --> 01:20:28,490
-You already used Heung-min last week.
-Do you only have Heung-min and Kang-in?

2091
01:20:28,557 --> 01:20:32,060
-Someone else, please.
-There are many other players on the team.

2092
01:20:32,127 --> 01:20:33,595
Or you can use the opponents.

2093
01:20:33,662 --> 01:20:35,163
Is this fun for you?

2094
01:20:35,597 --> 01:20:37,799
CRY-LAUGHING…

2095
01:20:37,866 --> 01:20:40,735
Does it taste like we can beat Mexico?

2096
01:20:40,802 --> 01:20:42,037
He's right.

2097
01:20:42,103 --> 01:20:47,442
-Mexico wears a green uniform like this.
-Yes, they do!

2098
01:20:48,009 --> 01:20:49,411
Does it taste like we can beat Mexico?

2099
01:20:49,477 --> 01:20:50,612
Can we seize the game?

2100
01:20:50,679 --> 01:20:52,013
Can we defeat them?

2101
01:20:52,080 --> 01:20:53,348
He's thinking.

2102
01:20:53,415 --> 01:20:56,318
-If our team gets to play…
-He's starting.

2103
01:20:56,384 --> 01:20:59,454
…after eating this dish,

2104
01:20:59,521 --> 01:21:01,089
we'll trample all over them.

2105
01:21:01,890 --> 01:21:03,091
The taste that can subdue them.

2106
01:21:03,158 --> 01:21:04,860
I prepared that dish

2107
01:21:04,926 --> 01:21:09,264
-hoping our team would gnaw on Mexico.
-To gnaw on Mexico?

2108
01:21:09,331 --> 01:21:10,832
Is the cheese Czech Republic?

2109
01:21:11,766 --> 01:21:12,601
Yes.

2110
01:21:13,635 --> 01:21:15,136
Czech rhymes with cheddar.

2111
01:21:15,203 --> 01:21:18,173
-Cheese stands for the Czech Republic.
-And Mexico is gone too.

2112
01:21:18,240 --> 01:21:21,176
SOUNDS PLAUSIBLE

2113
01:21:21,943 --> 01:21:23,612
There's no South Africa.

2114
01:21:24,479 --> 01:21:26,348
The sauce is yellow, actually.

2115
01:21:26,982 --> 01:21:28,917
-It's all in the dish.
-You should finish it.

2116
01:21:28,984 --> 01:21:33,421
I'll think of this sauce as South Africa.

2117
01:21:33,488 --> 01:21:36,258
I really love to chew on stuff.

2118
01:21:36,858 --> 01:21:39,494
He likes to chew things
and to chew people out.

2119
01:21:39,561 --> 01:21:41,796
He'll chew South Africa into pieces.

2120
01:21:41,863 --> 01:21:45,500
-You're now watching Manager Choi…
-Destroying South Africa.

2121
01:21:45,567 --> 01:21:46,534
That's right.

2122
01:21:48,136 --> 01:21:49,404
Is this funny to you?

2123
01:21:51,806 --> 01:21:53,909
VERY MUCH SO

2124
01:21:53,975 --> 01:21:55,076
"Is this funny to you?"

2125
01:21:55,143 --> 01:21:58,113
-Bellingham.
-What was Bellingham about?

2126
01:21:58,179 --> 01:21:59,781
He's a national English soccer player,

2127
01:21:59,848 --> 01:22:02,751
and his presence is the key

2128
01:22:02,817 --> 01:22:05,120
to Real Madrid's performance.

2129
01:22:05,186 --> 01:22:06,688
The difference is huge.

2130
01:22:06,755 --> 01:22:07,656
And?

2131
01:22:09,925 --> 01:22:11,693
I don't think this is it.

2132
01:22:11,760 --> 01:22:13,695
Where can he apply that?

2133
01:22:13,762 --> 01:22:16,464
HAS BELLINGHAM LOST HIS WAY?

2134
01:22:16,531 --> 01:22:19,067
-He's probably the duck.
-The duck.

2135
01:22:19,134 --> 01:22:21,536
The duck was like Bellingham.

2136
01:22:21,603 --> 01:22:25,073
What does he mean,
"the duck was like Bellingham"?

2137
01:22:25,140 --> 01:22:26,775
Let's call it a day.

2138
01:22:28,076 --> 01:22:30,078
A BIG APPLAUSE

2139
01:22:30,145 --> 01:22:32,580
CHOIPT DID HIS BEST

2140
01:22:32,647 --> 01:22:35,617
He did everything he had prepared.
A thumbs-up from Manager Park.

2141
01:22:35,684 --> 01:22:36,718
That's Manager Choi.

2142
01:22:36,785 --> 01:22:39,854
It's now time to choose between the two.

2143
01:22:39,921 --> 01:22:40,989
<i>Press one for Jung Ho-young</i>

2144
01:22:42,123 --> 01:22:43,291
<i>and two for Choi Hyun-suk.</i>

2145
01:22:44,426 --> 01:22:45,894
Make your decision

2146
01:22:45,961 --> 01:22:48,196
and press the button!

2147
01:22:48,263 --> 01:22:50,699
One for Ho-young, two for Hyun-suk.

2148
01:22:50,765 --> 01:22:52,500
I've made my choice.

2149
01:22:52,567 --> 01:22:53,868
-Are you done?
-Yes.

2150
01:22:53,935 --> 01:22:55,971
Who did Manager Choi choose?

2151
01:22:56,037 --> 01:22:58,373
Let's find out the result!

2152
01:22:59,407 --> 01:23:01,943
A Dish to Raise House Ent. CEO's Prestige.

2153
01:23:02,010 --> 01:23:04,913
If Hyun-suk wins,

2154
01:23:04,980 --> 01:23:09,150
Ho-young will be banned
from using social media for a week.

2155
01:23:09,217 --> 01:23:10,919
If Ho-young wins,

2156
01:23:10,986 --> 01:23:14,489
he'll make Chef Hyun-suk leave
nice comments on his posts for a week.

2157
01:23:14,556 --> 01:23:16,124
Who did Manager Choi Yong-soo pick?

2158
01:23:16,191 --> 01:23:17,692
Who is it?

2159
01:23:17,759 --> 01:23:19,260
Who won?

2160
01:23:19,327 --> 01:23:20,729
WHO RAISED HIS PRESTIGE?

2161
01:23:21,563 --> 01:23:22,397
What's the result?

2162
01:23:22,464 --> 01:23:24,666
JUNG HO-YOUNG WINS

2163
01:23:24,733 --> 01:23:25,834
CHEF HO-YOUNG WINS

2164
01:23:25,900 --> 01:23:27,102
Whoa!

2165
01:23:27,168 --> 01:23:28,870
-I'm so glad.
-Ho-young won.

2166
01:23:28,937 --> 01:23:31,206
THE SOCIAL MEDIA ADDICT WAS SAVED

2167
01:23:31,272 --> 01:23:32,440
Ho-young won.

2168
01:23:32,807 --> 01:23:35,243
HAS TO WRITE POSITIVE COMMENTS FOR A WEEK

2169
01:23:35,310 --> 01:23:38,380
He was seriously scared
that he'd have to get off social media.

2170
01:23:38,446 --> 01:23:40,682
-He got to stay on social media.
-Seriously.

2171
01:23:40,749 --> 01:23:44,119
-He's happier now than in <i>CCW2</i>.
-Yes, really.

2172
01:23:44,185 --> 01:23:46,354
Of course, I love duck.

2173
01:23:47,222 --> 01:23:51,226
But I loved the different mix
of restorative ingredients

2174
01:23:51,292 --> 01:23:52,861
served with rice.

2175
01:23:52,927 --> 01:23:55,563
-You simply liked that more.
-Yes.

2176
01:23:55,630 --> 01:23:59,034
Ho-young's victory over Hyun-suk

2177
01:23:59,100 --> 01:24:01,069
put them in a tie with five stars.

2178
01:24:01,136 --> 01:24:03,538
They're now neck-and-neck.

2179
01:24:03,605 --> 01:24:06,741
Also, you can stay on social media.

2180
01:24:06,808 --> 01:24:08,043
Let's hear from him.

2181
01:24:08,109 --> 01:24:11,613
Thank you very much for the star.

2182
01:24:11,679 --> 01:24:15,984
I love winning stars, but I'm just so glad
I can keep posting on my social media.

2183
01:24:16,051 --> 01:24:18,987
-It would've been fun to ban him though.
-What a shame.

2184
01:24:19,054 --> 01:24:20,822
Hyun-suk, for a week,

2185
01:24:20,889 --> 01:24:24,359
-you have to like his posts.
-And write comments.

2186
01:24:24,426 --> 01:24:25,960
Can I upload three posts a day?

2187
01:24:27,462 --> 01:24:29,297
You have to comment on every single post.

2188
01:24:29,364 --> 01:24:32,000
I don't mind not winning a star.

2189
01:24:32,067 --> 01:24:36,171
But I never do anything like that
when I'm on social media.

2190
01:24:36,237 --> 01:24:37,439
But you have to.

2191
01:24:37,505 --> 01:24:40,075
Why did you make the bet?

2192
01:24:40,141 --> 01:24:43,445
Please put a star on Chef Ho-young!

2193
01:24:43,511 --> 01:24:46,181
Manager Choi Yong-soo chose Ho-young!

2194
01:24:47,015 --> 01:24:48,049
He's now in fourth place

2195
01:24:48,116 --> 01:24:50,585
with five stars!

2196
01:24:50,652 --> 01:24:52,120
Congratulations!

2197
01:24:52,187 --> 01:24:54,956
COMING UP: PREVIEW FOR NAMKOONG MIN
AND KIM DAE-MYUNG'S EPISODE

2198
01:24:55,457 --> 01:24:57,158
Please welcome today's fridge owners!

2199
01:24:57,225 --> 01:24:59,894
Namkoong Min and Kim Dae-myung, welcome!

2200
01:24:59,961 --> 01:25:02,397
You've won three Grand Prizes in acting
for <i>Stove League</i>,

2201
01:25:02,464 --> 01:25:04,232
<i>The Veil, </i>and <i>My Dearest.</i>

2202
01:25:04,299 --> 01:25:06,935
I'm the type
who gets physically ready first.

2203
01:25:07,001 --> 01:25:08,470
-He has great self-control.
-He does.

2204
01:25:08,536 --> 01:25:10,338
I don't think I particularly like it.

2205
01:25:10,405 --> 01:25:12,607
I like food that makes you uglier.

2206
01:25:12,674 --> 01:25:14,142
-Food that makes you uglier?
-Food that makes you uglier?

2207
01:25:14,209 --> 01:25:16,711
I don't care how it changes my looks.

2208
01:25:16,778 --> 01:25:19,581
I want to eat something
that's purely and instinctively delicious.

2209
01:25:19,647 --> 01:25:20,815
Make him ugly.

2210
01:25:20,882 --> 01:25:23,084
-That's strong.
-He's not even hiding it.

2211
01:25:23,151 --> 01:25:25,253
-That food looks ugly.
-You may not wake up tomorrow.

2212
01:25:25,653 --> 01:25:26,688
SCARED

2213
01:25:26,754 --> 01:25:29,958
Everyone here in the studio
voted by secret ballot.

2214
01:25:30,024 --> 01:25:31,392
And this is the result.

2215
01:25:33,161 --> 01:25:35,063
A TWIST IN THE RESULT

2216
01:25:35,330 --> 01:25:36,764
WHO WAS CHOSEN BY EVERYONE?

2217
01:25:36,998 --> 01:25:38,032
KIM POONG, THE CHIEF GATEKEEPER

2218
01:25:38,233 --> 01:25:39,334
YOU CAN'T GET PAST HIM THAT EASILY

2219
01:25:39,634 --> 01:25:40,935
BUT SHE'S NOT AN EASY FIGHT

2220
01:25:41,202 --> 01:25:42,604
CHOPS WITHOUT HESITATING

2221
01:25:42,804 --> 01:25:43,905
SO THAT'S HOW IT'S GOING TO BE?

2222
01:25:44,272 --> 01:25:45,406
FIGHTS WITH HIS FREE SPIRIT

2223
01:25:45,773 --> 01:25:46,808
WHEN MOON-JUNG USES A SKILL

2224
01:25:47,008 --> 01:25:48,576
HE COPIES AND LEARNS IT IMMEDIATELY

2225
01:25:48,810 --> 01:25:49,811
MET THE TOUGHEST OPPONENT

2226
01:25:50,044 --> 01:25:51,045
ROAD TO KIM POONG

2227
01:25:51,246 --> 01:25:52,347
WILL SHE PASS THE TEST?

2228
01:25:55,483 --> 01:25:58,853
<i>Abracadabra, abra</i>

2229
01:25:58,920 --> 01:26:02,624
<i>Absolutely abracadabra</i>

2230
01:26:12,233 --> 01:26:17,005
Subtitle translation by: Eunsook Youn
